Job_desc:
Maintaining the filing system, filing, and retrieving documents;
,Serving as Alternate Document Control Officer and providing access to secure safe and secure computer network;
,Administers, processes and tracks all LW TDY requests/Transportation requests, including coordination with Finance, National Support Units etc.;
,Assisting in monitoring and ensuring appropriate update to Unit Deployment Manager (UDM) databases etc.;
,Operating all types of standard office equipment, including PC-based applications on classified and unclassified systems using a full suite of professional office software;
,Assisting in organizing/maintaining the LW calendars and LW suspense system in support of the LW HQ staff functions and ensuring the awareness of concerned staff members;
,Preparing and typing correspondence, memoranda, letters, reports, talking papers, briefings and other forms of correspondence from draft;
,Drafting correspondence from oral instructions or written notes;
,Reviewing correspondence requiring signature for proper format and grammar;
,Taking, preparing, coordinating and distributing minutes of lengthy and technically complex meetings and conferences;
,Reviewing, processing and routing of all command group incoming and outgoing mail including faxes, local and external e-mail;
,Responding to telephones and visitors’ information and managing messages received;
,Maintaining, monitoring command group suspense’s, appointments and schedules and ensuring the awareness of concerned staff members;
,Collecting information and researching issues, as directed;
,Compiling and preparing statistical information, as directed;
,Performing protocol related duties, attending to military visitors, dignitaries, and other guests;
,Providing unofficial language translation support (English/German);
,Acting as requisitioning focal point for administrative forms and publications and organization equipment custodian account;
,Making travel arrangements and preparing itineraries and travel orders.<br/>
,Good working knowledge of office management procedures and administrative principles acquired through at least 3 years of related, current professional experience;
,Secondary education and completed basic vocational training in an administrative field;
,Secondary education and basic training in business administration, public administration or related discipline for specific task related skills, with two years experience;
,The work, both oral and written, in this post and in this Headquarters as a whole, is conducted mainly in English and sufficient proficiency is therefore essential;
,Adequate Knowledge of Standard Automatic Data Processing (ADP) programs is required.<br/>
,Previous NATO assignment;
,Administrative experience working in an international/military environment;
,Completed advanced vocational training in an administrative field.<br/>
,Excellent tax-free salary, including (where eligible) expatriation, family and children's allowances and additional privileges for expatriate staff;
,Education allowance for children (where appropriate) and an excellent private health insurance scheme;
,Generous annual leave and home leave (if eligible);
,Retirement Pension Plan.<br/>

Establishing and actioning the financial aspects of contracts with HN authorities, including all mandatory data processing in the various logistical (PILS) and financial (NAFS) systems for provision of funds, receipts, payments, etc.;
,Collecting data for reimbursable projects (works executed by HN Construction Agency and/or Bw-DLZ (Bundeswehrdienstleistungszentrum-German armed forces location management) for agencies not eligible for NATO funds);
,Operating of all types of standard office equipment;
,Providing general administrative support to the office;
,Assisting with the collection, retrieval and compiling of statistical information, and providing project support to the office;
,Ordering and maintaining forms and publications;
,Establishing and maintaining contacts with national/international authorities;
,Typing work orders to Bw-DLZ and surveying the work order list;
,Co-ordinating of meetings and appointments for the Branch Head (Infrastructure) and his/her deputy;<br/>
,Experience in accounting or financial management is essential;
,Secondary education and basic training is word-processing, accounting, management information systems, public administration, finance, management, business administration or related discipline for specific task related skills, with 2 years' experience;
,The work both oral and written, in this post and in this Headquarters as a whole, is conducted mainly in English therefore adequate English proficiency is essential;
,German SLP 3333 is required for incumbent to perform assigned duties;
,Adequate knowledge of Automated Data Processing (ADP) systems is required.<br/>
,Previous NATO assignment;
,Experience working in an international/military environment;
,Successful training in IT based financial/accounting and supply systems;
,Experience in Project and/or Programme Management;
,Experience in Risk Management;
,Experience in Information and Knowledge Management;
,Experience in Office Management support.<br/>
,Excellent tax-free salary, including (where eligible) expatriation, family and children's allowances and additional privileges for expatriate staff;
,Education allowance for children (where appropriate) and an excellent private health insurance scheme;
,Generous annual leave and home leave (if eligible);
,Retirement Pension Plan.<br/>

Required to cross-train and qualify in all section assigned trades;
,Identifying, proposing and evaluating technical and/or software data changes and modifications;
,Assisting in analyzing and interpreting all jobs relevant Mission and Work Data to identify problem and trend areas with respect to E-3A a/c and simulator computer data processing/data display, ESM sensor LAIRCM systems and components Software, Hardware and Training;
,Performing inspections and maintenance of on-board a/c fibre optic networks including the utilization of state-of-the-art test/calibration equipment;
,Assisting during modernizations at engineering level, throughout the full implementation phase;
,Assisting in identifying requirements and introducing Proposed Technical Solutions;
,Occasionally interfacing with internal and external functional elements regarding maintenance of Computer/Display &amp; ESM/LAIRCM equipment for the E-3A and mission simulator weapon systems;
,Assisting in planning and coordinating daily work details according to established priorities;
,Occasionally coordinating and scheduling short term maintenance and modernization activities in order to meet mission requirements;
,Performing dispatcher duties;
,Maintaining and monitoring inspection and maintenance forms, records and databases;
,Functioning as technical publications, special test equipment, Consolidated Tool Kit (CTK) and tool monitor;
,As functional area subject matter expert (SME), provides the LW Training Section inputs on training analysis, required level of learning and method of delivery related aspects;
,As functional area subject matter expert (SME), supports other LW training courses as directed;
,Conducting OJT and advises newly assigned personnel;
,Assisting in the establishment and improvement of preventative and corrective maintenance procedures;
,Assisting other technicians in performing work on other E-3A a/c systems and maintaining other E-3A a/c electronic systems when appropriately trained and/or qualified;
,Operating diagnostic electronic and computer based test equipment;
,Operating logistics related computer terminals;
,Operating motor vehicles, support and test equipment;
,Supporting other squadron activities and assisting in special projects;
,Performing general housekeeping duties, including ground snow/ice removal.<br/>
,Very good working knowledge of a/c electronics, preferably electronic sensor systems, electronic data processing and data display systems maintenance;
,Good working knowledge of and professional experience in interpreting technical publications and independently analyzing and rectifying complex technical problems;
,Experience in utilizing operational, diagnostic, and utility software programmes for fault detection and isolation;
,Higher Secondary education and completed intermediate vocational training in a/c electronics systems maintenance encompassing the theory of basic electronics, electro-mechanical devices, solid-state components and digital techniques, RF principles, basic computer network techniques or Secondary education and completed appropriate advanced vocational training with at least 2 years of post-related, current professional experience;
,Driving license equivalent to European Class B;
,Adequate knowledge of Standard Automatic Data Processing (ADP) programmes is required;
,The work, both oral and written, in this post and in this Headquarters as a whole, is conducted mainly in English and sufficient proficiency is therefore essential.<br/>
,Previous NATO assignment;
,Experience working in an international/military environment;
,Knowledge of/professional experience in maintaining a/c electronic systems, preferably computer and data display systems;
,Knowledge of/experience in utilizing state of the art digital/analogue test equipment;
,Knowledge of state of the art data bus technology;
,Knowledge of Local Area Networks (LAN), of fibre optics and of UNIX network/operating systems;
,Experience in basic soldering techniques;
,Training in a/c electronic systems, preferably in computer and data display and/or electronic sensor systems maint enance.<br/>
,Excellent tax-free salary, including (where eligible) expatriation, family and children's allowances and additional privileges for expatriate staff;
,Education allowance for children (where appropriate) and an excellent private health insurance scheme;
,Generous annual leave and home leave (if eligible);
,Retirement Pension Plan.<br/>
